  "prompt": "Can one change branch from biotechnology engineering to engineering physics in IIT Roorkee?",
  "response": "At IIT Roorkee, students typically cannot change branches from one engineering discipline to another after the first year, as branch transfers are generally not allowed. However, policies regarding branch changes can vary by institution and over time, so it is advisable to check the latest regulations directly from the IIT Roorkee academic office or their official website for the most current and specific guidelines related to branch changes.\n\nIn some cases, if students perform exceptionally well academically and meet other requirements, there might be opportunities for branch changes within certain limits. However, this is usually subject to availability and institutional rules. Always consult official sources for the most accurate information.",
